We choose the term descriptor to indicate generically the element used to bind/map/qualify a value with respect to its entity. Practically, this term maps to

  • "Field" in Object Oriented Programming;
  • "Predicate" in First Order Logic
  • Column identifier (Attribute) in Relation Database terminology
  • rdf:Property in the Resource Description Framework

This relation is needed to generically express comparison of data nodes with relation to the domain covered.

Similar relations might refer to other features, being it structural (they share schema elements), physical (they are both in XML) or related to the domain (they both talk about Music Artists) - just to make few examples.. We might want to specify other kind of features, covering: ownership (sameOwner), meta-model (sameMetaModel), syntax (sameSyntax), accessMethod (sameAccessMethod), license (compatibleLicense, sameLicense), policies (?).
